9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 595, L.D. 930, “An Act to Amend the
10 Law Governing Items Identified as Prison Contraband”
11 Amend the bill by striking out all of section 2 and inserting the following:
12 'Sec. 2. 17-A MRSA §757, sub-§4 is enacted to read:
13 4. If the prison contraband under subsection 1, paragraph B is electronic contraband
14 that is not intended to be used to commit a separate crime, trafficking in prison contraband
15 is a Class D crime. For purposes of this subsection, "electronic contraband" means a mobile
16 telephone or other handheld electronic communication device not authorized or issued by
17 the custodial authority.
18 Sec. 3. 17-A MRSA §757-A, as enacted by PL 2001, c. 386, §2, is amended to read:
19 §757-A. Trafficking of tobacco or vaping device in adult correctional facilities
20 1. A person is guilty of trafficking tobacco or a vaping device in an adult correctional
21 facility if:
22 A. That person intentionally conveys or attempts to convey tobacco or, tobacco
23 products or a vaping device to a person confined in an adult correctional facility that
24 has banned the use of tobacco or, tobacco products or vaping devices by prisoners; or
25 B. That person is confined in an adult correctional facility that has banned the use of
26 tobacco or, tobacco products or vaping devices by prisoners and the person
27 intentionally obtains or possesses tobacco or, tobacco products or a vaping device.
28 2. As used in this section, "adult correctional facility" means a county jail or
29 correctional facility other than a juvenile facility under the control of the Department of
30 Corrections and "vaping device" means a device, also known as a vape, e-cigarette,
31 electronic cigarette or electronic vaporizer, that simulates smoking using an atomizer, a
32 power source such as a battery and a container such as a cartridge or a tank and is used for
33 ingesting any substance, including a drug identified in section 1101, subsection 11.
